article.headline: Hurricanes bolt to big lead and hold on
article.linkText: Broussard leads Miami over West Virginia
article.story:
CORAL GABLES, Fla. (AP) -- Chanivia Broussard scored 25 points to
lead Miami (No. 19 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP), which withstood a late rally by West Virginia in an 82-74 victory Saturday night.

Miami (21-5, 10-5 Big East) led by as many as 20 points in the
second half, but West Virginia put together a 12-2 run and got to
74-68 on Kate Bulger's 3-pointer with 37 seconds remaining. She had
eight 3-pointers -- including four in the final 1:42 -- and finished
with 28 points for West Virginia (19-8, 10-5).

Yalonda McCormick hit all six of her free-throw attempts in the
final 32 seconds to seal the victory for Miami. She finished with 14
points.

The Mountaineers trailed early but got to 19-17 on a 3-pointer
by Bulger with 9:30 remaining in the first half. Miami closed the
half with an 18-9 run for a 37-26 lead at the break.

The Hurricanes opened the second half with a 9-0 run to take a
20-point lead, and West Virginia trailed 72-56 when Broussard
fouled out with 2:12 left to play.

Melissa Knight, Shaquana Wilkins and Tamara James added 12
points apiece for Miami.
